Title Review:
Failed program The idea of â€‹â€‹the program is that it alerts you before the problem occurs, and this is not guaranteed, neither on the quarantined, nor the person who is close to the quarantined
There is a long delay in receiving alerts, as it is possible for a patient to be mixed with a stone, and the warning is not given to both of them except after the ax topples the head
Unfortunately, because you entered your data, they will recite you and humiliate you as soon as you approached a sick person who was not quarantined, and they quarantine you as a precaution, and you are jubilant because the program did not alert you immediately
The program guarantees a government response, but it is too late.

I mean, if I approached a normal sick person, I would turn back the house and count all my family, and after a week they would call and say: Come, you and your family, and everyone near you to stone
